original_recipe:
1. Grind poppy seeds into a paste.
2. Set aside.
3. In a large frying pan , sautÃ© onions and green chillies in oil until golden brown.
4. Add ginger and garlic and continue to sautÃ©.
5. Add poppy seed paste and chicken , continuing to sautÃ©.
6. Stir all together ; after chicken is well mixed with the sauce , add the cayenne pepper and pour water over the mixture.
7. Cover frying pan and let simmer about 15 minutes , until chicken is cooked through.
8. After chicken is ' well-boiled ' ( the oil should be floating on top of the frying pan liquid ) , add the garam masala and turmeric and turn off the heat.
9. Season with salt to taste.
10. Stir all together and serve.
